    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Currently, there is a `TextYankPost` event to detect when text is yanked or deleted. It is useful to have similar events to detect when text is put in the buffer (for example, with `p` or `:m`).\r\n\r\n`TextPutPre` and `TextPutPost` were mentioned in <https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/4448/>.\r\n\r\nI don't know if `TextPutPre` is really necessary.\r\n\r\n`TextPutPost` should be triggered in the [`do_put` function](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/v0.5.0/src/nvim/ops.c#L2809-L2816), after updating the `'[` and `']` markers.\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\n\r\nI wrote a plugin to highlight text when it is pasted from the clipboard. It uses the [paste handler](https://neovim.io/doc/user/lua.html#vim.paste%28%29) to detect when something is pasted ([code](https://github.com/ayosec/hltermpaste.vim/blob/0.2/lua/hltermpaste.lua#L1-L24)). However, there is no way to detect when a user put something using a command (for example, `\"xp` to put contents of the register `x`).\r\n\r\nWith the `TextPutPost` autocommand event, it will possible to handle those cases. \r\n\r\nAlso, it can be useful to include a default implementation for this event, similar to [`vim.highlight.on_yank()`](https://neovim.io/doc/user/lua.html#vim.highlight.on_yank%28%29) for `TextYankPost`.\r\n",
