            "body": "> does the `TextChanged` event help?\r\n\r\n`TextChanged` is _very_ close to what I expect. The only missing feature is a way to detect if the change is from a *put* command (like `p` or `\"rgP`), or from anything else (like text added in INSERT mode, the undo action, etc).\r\n\r\nMaybe, instead of adding new events, a better solution is to add `v:event` data to `TextChanged`, similar to what is available for [`TextYankPost`]. Thus, we can use `v:event.operator == 'p'` (or something like that) to detect if the event is triggered by a *put* command.\r\n\r\n[`TextYankPost`]: https://neovim.io/doc/user/autocmd.html#TextYankPost\r\n\r\n",
